SIMPLE: rescript
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rescript
<hw>Re"script</hw> <pr>(r?"skr?pt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rescriptum</ets>: cf. F. <ets>rescrit</ets>, formerly also spelt
<ets>rescript</ets>. See <er>Rescribe</er>,<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom.Antiq.)</fld> <def>The answer of an emperor
when formallyconsulted by particular persons on some difficult question;
hence, an edict or decree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In their <qex>rescripts</qex> and other ordinances, the Roman
emperors spoke in the plural number.</q> <rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld> <def>The official written answer of
the pope upon a question of canon law, or morals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A counterpart.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rescription</ent>⟦br⟧
